Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp

Class CompiledAction

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.Action
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp.CompiledAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
CompiledEvent, Event, Logical, Simplifiable, Signed, Unique, Serializable, Comparable<Logical>
public class CompiledAction extends Action implements CompiledEvent
A compiled action is a ground action which defines a unique ID number that corresponds to the action's index in its compiled problem's set of events, whose precondition and observation function are in disjunctive normal form, and whose effect is a clause.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • getEffect

      public Clause<Effect> getEffect(Fluent fluent)
      Description copied from interface: CompiledEvent
      Returns a clause composed of every effect in this event's effect that has the given fluent as its fluent. The returned clause may be empty if this event does not affect the given fluent, or it may have several atoms if this event has several conditional effects which might affect the given fluent.
      Specified by:
      getEffect in interface CompiledEvent
      Parameters:
      fluent - the fluent which this event may affect
      Returns:
      a clause of all ways this event could affect the given fluent
